properties.areaDesc: Southern Sacramento Valley; Northern San Joaquin Valley; Carquinez Strait and Delta
properties.headline: Freeze Warning issued February 3 at 12:33PM PST until February 4 at 9:00AM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Cold Morning Low Temperatures in the Northern San Joaquin
Valley...

.A cold air mass over the Northern San Joaquin Valley will result
in 3 to 5 hours of sub-freezing temperatures early Tuesday morning.
This could harm or damage crops and plants sensitive to freezing
temperatures.

The Freeze Warning also includes a small portion of the East Delta
and the extreme southern portion of the southern Sacramento Valley.
The gusty northerly winds this afternoon are expected to diminish
early Tuesday morning in this area.

Don't forget about pets...make sure they have shelter from the cold.

* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures from 26 to 30 early Tuesday
morning.

* WHERE...Extreme Southern Sacramento Valley, Extreme southeast
portion of the Delta and the Northern San Joaquin Valley
Counties.

* WHEN...From 4 AM to 9 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions may harm or damage crops
or other sensitive vegetation.
properties.instruction:
Take steps to protect crops and tender plants from the cold. Don't
forget to provide shelter for your pets from the cold.

NWSheadline: FREEZE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM TO 9 AM PST TUESDAY
